snippet: At their training camp in Cortland, N.Y., the Jets and their No. 2 quarterback, Tim Tebow, worked on Wildcat plays that news media members in attendance were prohibited from describing.
abstract: Reporters attending New York Jets practice are restricted from divulging formations or personnel used in the team's version of the Wildcat offense, for which they had acquired backup quarterback Tim Tebow.
lead_paragraph: At their training camp in Cortland, N.Y., the Jets and their No. 2 quarterback, Tim Tebow, worked on Wildcat plays that news media members in attendance were prohibited from describing.

headline.seo: Tim Tebow and Jets Run Wildcat in Practice
headline.main: Jets Keeping Wildcat a Secret of Sorts
headline.print_headline: Jets Are Keeping Wildcat Plays and Players’ Roles a Secret of Sorts
